description:
ROOT CAUSE: src/docker_backend.rs:511-570 release_stale_slots_from_with_containers_for, Path 1 (lines 538-544) reclaims a slot whenever the recorded runner_id is missing from live_runners (the GH API list) — but does NOT check whether a local container is alive. Race window:
1. spawn_one_runner (line 951) does docker run; container created in <1s, Runner.Worker inside starts registering with GH via JIT config.
2. record_slot_runner_id_for (line 964) writes runner_id to slot_assignments.toml IMMEDIATELY after docker run returns.
3. JIT registration propagation through GH API takes 5-30s.
4. Next release_stale_slots cycle (every 30s, line 296 calls list_runners) sees live_ids.contains(&rid)==false (registration not yet visible), reclaims the slot.
5. Next ensure_count sees no slot ownership, respawns the same slot, KILLS the just-started container, retries JIT, repeat.

EVIDENCE (jeff-ubuntu daemon journal, 21:50-21:55 PDT 2026-07-08): every 30s a reclaim+respawn cycle. Reclaim counts of 2/4/6/4/5/1/1/2 within 8 minutes. By 21:53 only 11/16 Linux registered; missing c-15 with container up, Runner.Worker alive, JIT propagation still in flight. INV-1 violation 21:54:48: busy=16/22 registered=18 queued_jobs=10 fail_class=missing-registration.

FIX: Extend Path 1 safety net to mirror sub-pass 3 (line 554-565) — before reclaiming when !live_ids.contains(&rid), check if a local container with the expected name is alive. If yes, skip reclaim (the runner is mid-registration; do not kill it before it can serve jobs).

  } else if let Ok(rid) = id_str.parse::<u64>() {
      if !live_ids.contains(&rid) {
          let expected_name = runner_name_from_prefix(runner_prefix, slot_n);
          if let Some(local_names) = local_container_names {
              if local_names.contains(&expected_name) {
                  // registration in flight; wait for it
                  continue;
              }
          }
          release_slot_for(cfg, slot_n)?;
          reclaimed += 1;
      }

BLAST-RADIUS: strictly more conservative (fewer reclaims). Truly stale ID with no container: still reclaimed. Truly stale ID whose container is dead: still reclaimed. Only the 'container alive + runner_id not yet in API' case is preserved.

DISTINCT FROM Mac slot-drift (bead jleechan-kbd): kbd targets empty-id reservation path (lines 531-537). This targets non-empty-id-but-not-yet-propagated path (lines 538-544). Different code paths, different timing windows. jleechan-kbd does NOT cover this. Both fixes needed.

LINKED: jleechan-g5h (parent investigation), jleechan-kbd (Mac fix). Provenance: 2026-07-08, diagnosed by linux-missing-reg-investigator sidekick via /tmp/worldai/sidekick/linux-missing-reg-12h/STATE.md.
